records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

Received and Filed: Proposed Order of Commitment for Treatment

Defendant Jose J Gaeta Huerta in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael B Plaisted in court for Jose J Gaeta Huerta.  Attorney Francesco Mineo in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a competency hearing.  Sworn for the State: Doctor Alix Shepherd (Examining Psychologist).  Court attempts colloquy with Mr. Huerta and finds the defendant stands mute on the issue of competency.  Court finds Mr. Huerta NOT COMPETENT to proceed or assist in his own defense.  Court suspends the proceedings and orders the defendant COMMITTED under the Department of Health Services. 
 Court further orders the defendant transported FORTHWITH.  Order of Commitment for Treatment signed and filed by the Court.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for January 13, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Competency hearing scheduled for October 12, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Jose J Gaeta Huerta in court, appear by video with attorney Michael B Plaisted, appear by video.  Defendant Jose J Gaeta Huerta in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge John Frank, Room 608 Court House.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department. Court will appoint counsel for Defendant.  The Court appoints Attorney Michael Plaisted to represent defendant at the rate of $100 per hour;  Attorney Plaisted NOT present in court but was contacted by the deputy clerk during the hearing and accepted the appointment. 

Court finds that the defendant does not have to repay the County.  Order Appointing Counsel to be forwarded to the Court for Judge's signature.  

Court orders case adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.
